cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with Internet censorship and circumvention techniques. It could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it involves measuring the availability of a specific network. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves a network of distributed VPN servers. The paper also touches upon issues related to cyber security (cs.CY) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it measures the availability of different I2P services.
